**Examplar Stage Statement** 
**Claim:** GMOs are a valuable tool alongside other agricultural advancements.
**Purpose:** propose => GMOs are a valuable tool alongside other agricultural advancements.;
**Content:** We support the motion that GMOs are beneficial.  As scientists and agricultural experts, we've seen firsthand the positive impact of this technology. GMOs are not a silver bullet, but a valuable tool alongside other agricultural advancements like plant breeding and organic farming.
**Argument:** The speaker supports the motion that GMOs are beneficial. The speaker has seen the positive impact of GMOs firsthand as scientists and agricultural experts. GMOs are a valuable tool alongside other agricultural advancements like plant breeding and organic farming. GMO technology is still in its infancy, with immense potential yet to be realized. Voting against GMOs shuts the door on future innovations.

**Claim:** GMOs have a 20+ year safety record with no credible instances of food or feed safety issues and a strong scientific consensus supports this conclusion.
**Purpose:** propose => GMOs have a 20+ year safety record with no credible instances of food or feed safety issues and a strong scientific consensus supports this conclusion.;
**Content:** Let's address safety, a top priority.  GMOs have a 20+ year safety record, with no credible instances of food or feed safety issues. This isn't just our opinion; there's a strong scientific consensus, similar to the consensus on climate change.  These foods are among the most thoroughly studied in our food supply.  Studies, including meta-analyses of over 1,700 scientific records and assessments of livestock consuming GMO feed for over a decade, confirm their safety. Major scientific organizations, including the AAAS, WHO, AMA, and National Academies, support this conclusion.
**Argument:** GMOs have a 20+ year safety record with no credible instances of food or feed safety issues. There is a strong scientific consensus that GMOs are safe, similar to the consensus on climate change. GMOs are among the most thoroughly studied foods. Studies, including meta-analyses of over 1,700 scientific records and assessments of livestock consuming GMO feed for over a decade, confirm their safety. Major scientific organizations, including the AAAS, WHO, AMA, and National Academies, support this conclusion. GMO technology has been in use since the 1970s with a proven safety record. Regulatory bodies like USDA, EPA, and FDA provide extensive oversight, ensuring safety. Importing countries conduct independent assessments. Thousands of academic studies and major scientific organizations confirm the safety of GMO products. 20 years of data and thousands of studies, including long-term animal studies, show no unique safety concerns. There is a scientific consensus on GMO safety, similar to that on climate change.

**Claim:** Farmers have seen reduced pesticide use, increased yields, and higher profits from GMOs.
**Purpose:** propose => Farmers have seen reduced pesticide use, increased yields, and higher profits from GMOs.;
**Content:** Farmers wouldn't use GMOs if they didn't offer real benefits.  They've seen reduced pesticide use, increased yields (up 22% on average), and higher profits (up 68% on average).  These benefits are especially significant for smallholder farmers in developing countries. GMOs also enable no-till farming, preserving soil and reducing emissions.
**Argument:** Farmers have seen reduced pesticide use. Farmers have seen increased yields (up 22% on average). Farmers have seen higher profits (up 68% on average). These benefits are especially significant for smallholder farmers in developing countries. GMOs also enable no-till farming, preserving soil and reducing emissions. Bt crops reduce insecticide use, especially in developing nations (37% reduction). Herbicide-tolerant crops promote no-till farming, more than doubling its adoption since the mid-90s. No-till farming reduces erosion, moisture loss, and greenhouse gas emissions. Herbicide resistance is a challenge similar to antibiotic resistance, requiring innovation. Farmers are already using herbicide combinations as a best practice.

**Claim:** GMOs have broader applications beyond insect and herbicide resistance, including virus-resistant papaya, drought-resistant corn, and disease-resistant crops.
**Purpose:** propose => GMOs have broader applications beyond insect and herbicide resistance, including virus-resistant papaya, drought-resistant corn, and disease-resistant crops.;
**Content:** This technology has broader applications beyond insect and herbicide resistance.  Examples include virus-resistant papaya saving the Hawaiian papaya industry, drought-resistant corn, and disease-resistant crops crucial for food security in developing nations.  Publicly funded research is exploring disease-resistant livestock, nitrogen-efficient rice, and nutrient-rich cassava, among other applications. These advancements focus on using genetics rather than chemicals for disease control, aligning with sustainable agriculture goals.
**Argument:** GMOs have broader applications beyond insect and herbicide resistance. Examples include virus-resistant papaya saving the Hawaiian papaya industry. Examples include drought-resistant corn. Examples include disease-resistant crops crucial for food security in developing nations. Publicly funded research is exploring disease-resistant livestock, nitrogen-efficient rice, and nutrient-rich cassava. These advancements focus on using genetics rather than chemicals for disease control, aligning with sustainable agriculture goals.

**Claim:** GMOs can play a vital role in producing more food sustainably to address the growing global population and climate change.
**Purpose:** propose => GMOs can play a vital role in producing more food sustainably to address the growing global population and climate change.;
**Content:** The growing global population and climate change present a daunting challenge. We need every tool at our disposal. GMOs, when used responsibly alongside other approaches, can play a vital role in producing more food sustainably. We urge you to vote yes, embracing innovation to address the critical challenge of feeding the world.
**Argument:** The growing global population and climate change present a daunting challenge. We need every tool at our disposal. GMOs, when used responsibly alongside other approaches, can play a vital role in producing more food sustainably. Focusing solely on perceived risks ignores the real risk of hunger. GM technology is a breeding method with no demonstrated unique risks. Demanding further, costly studies without specific scientific justification is unproductive. GM technology, along with other approaches, is essential for addressing global food security and alleviating poverty. 70% of the world's poor are farmers, who would benefit from GM technology.
